OL,3,C27 children sign good behaviour
OL,4,Ccontracts after city centre trouble
OL,6,FTwenty-seven children as young as 12
OL,7,Fhave signed police contracts promising
OL,8,Fto behave after complaints of
OL,9,Fdrinking, intimidation and anti-social
OL,10,Fbehaviour in city centre shops.
OL,12,FThe acceptable behaviour contracts
OL,13,F(ABCs) specify agreed conduct -
OL,14,Fincluding curfews and limits on
OL,15,Fsocialising in groups - following
OL,16,Fproblems in Lincoln.
OL,18,FThose who have signed them - who are
OL,19,Faged 12 to 16 - admitted their
OL,20,Fbehaviour was unacceptable.
